Class Pirate

  • java.lang.Object
    • Pirate

  • public class Pirate
extends java.lang.Object
    Public class Pirate represents enemies in the game. It stores information of position of enemy on board, direction in which to move and if enemy has bin destroyed.
    Since:
    18/1/2019
    Version:
    1.0.0 (alfa)
    Author:
    Mirnel Bucan

      • returnDistance

        private int returnDistance(int xP,
                           int yP,
                           int yD,
                           int xD)
        Manhattan distance between two points across two-dimensional grid is just sum of theirs horizontal and vertical difference.
        Parameters:
        xP - Current player column position (or looked in 2D coordinated system , x coordinate)
        yP - Current player row position (or looked in 2D coordinated system , y coordinate)
        yD - Current pirate row position (or looked in 2D coordinated system , y coordinate)
        xD - Current pirate column position (or looked in 2D coordinated system , x coordinate)
        Returns:
        int Manhattan distance of player and pirate

      • newPosition

        void newPosition(int x1,
                 int y1)
        New position of pirate is minimum one amongst 8 possible steps. If there is more than one minimum, then we randomly pick one of them.
        Parameters:
        x1 - Represents current row of player on board.
        y1 - Represents current column of player on board.

      • randomIndex

        private int randomIndex(int[] niz,
                        int min)
        This function is used to simulate possibility of AI mistake. Since it would be almost impossible to win game if computer is constantly anticipating players every move without mistake.
        Parameters:
        niz - Is array possible moves to chose from
        min - Is minimal distance between player and pirate
        Returns:
        int Returns "choice" made randomly to move

      • getRandom01

        int getRandom01()
        This function is used to simulate that mistake, 25% chance to make wrong move.
        Returns:
        int Returns 0 if there is no mistake, 1 if mistake occurs .
